Biases in Triple Extraction Evaluation: LLMs may exhibit various types of biases; representation of the majority viewpoint being a common issue due to distributions prevalent within pretraining data [bender2021dangers], neglecting disagreements among multiple viewpoints (e.g. by majority voting) [davani2022dealing]. Prior works investigate individual factors (such as frequency) or LLM biases in other tasks [Mao-9881877], as well as knowledge retrieval [zhong2021factual].